<sect2 id="filters-noise-introduction">
  <title>Introduction</title>

  <indexterm>
    <primary>Filters</primary>
    <secondary>Noise</secondary>
    <tertiary>Introduction</tertiary>
  </indexterm>
  <para>
    Noise filters <emphasis>add</emphasis> noise to the active layer or to the
    selection. To <emphasis>remove</emphasis> small defects from an image, see
    the <link linkend="plug-in-despeckle">Despeckle</link> and
    <link linkend="gimp-filter-gaussian-blur-selective">Selective Gaussian
      Blur</link> filters.
  </para>

  <para>
    This category describes the following filters:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para><xref linkend="gimp-filter-noise-cie-lch"/></para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para><xref linkend="gimp-filter-noise-hsv"/></para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para><xref linkend="gimp-filter-noise-hurl"/></para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para><xref linkend="gimp-filter-noise-pick"/></para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para><xref linkend="gimp-filter-noise-rgb"/></para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para><xref linkend="gimp-filter-noise-slur"/></para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para><xref linkend="gimp-filter-noise-spread"/></para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>

</sect2>
